File. Pixabay/F1 Digitals JOHANNESBURG - One South Africa Movement continues its call for the matric pass mark to be increased from 30 to 50 percent. The movement unveiled what it calls an education 'rescue' plan on Thursday. READ: Matric results to be published It lists ten interventions for the country’s education system. Movement leader Mmusi Maimane says pupils need to be well prepared for the fourth industrial revolution.